The cost of COVID Pasco schools take $11 million hit | March 8 If everything that the governor says about vaccines is true, why are Pasco County public schools running a health care cost deficit of $11.3 in COVID-related claims for 2021 — 97 percent of which were “incurred by plan participants who identified themselves to their health providers as being unvaccinated”? I wish this governor would stop with the crazy conspiracy theorists and listen to the majority of well-respected scientists and epidemiologists who recommend vaccines for everyone. Touting papers that have not been peer reviewed is irresponsible. Ann Jamieson, St. Petersburg Brain shrinkage Kids could skip shots | March 8 The lead headline in Tuesday’s Tampa Bay Times was “Kids could skip shots,” a Florida plan to recommend that healthy kids not get COVID vaccinations. This was decided by Gov. Ron DeSantis and his surgeon general in direct contrast to guidelines published by the Centers for Disease Control and Prevention. And then in other news ... There was this headline in the same issue of the Times: “Study: Mild COVID can shrink the brain.” Are we Flori-duh? Marilyn S. Warner, Clearwater Putin’s catnip Should there be a no-fly zone over Ukraine? | PolitiFact, March 8 As we watch a large and well-armed country like Ukraine get pummeled by its larger neighbor, Russia, the non-NATO, non-EU counties of Moldova and Georgia will be catnip for Vladimir Putin. How will we view ourselves when this is all over? Tom Miller, Clearwater Stating the facts Trump muses on Russian War, praises Kim Jong Un | March 7 Former President Donald Trump describing Vladimir Putin and Kim Jong Un as “seriously tough,” “savvy” and “brilliant” is not praising them. It’s recognizing the attributes of your adversary and not underestimating their abilities. Jere White, Tampa